Birchview Elementary School
August 30 at 12:34 PM ¬∑

Hey Everyone!

I just wanted to pass along some information regarding some changes to the pick up and drop off process at Birchview.

This year, vehicles will enter the Birchview parking lot from the north entrance, and exit the parking lot to the east onto Hickory Street.

We are making these changes in response to a significant increase in the number of students who will be picked up and dropped off this year.

In an effort to maintain a safe and organized pick up/drop off environment, we ask for your patience and raised awareness during this new process.

Thank you, have a great rest of your day, and we can‚Äôt wait to see you around Noon tomorrow!

Edit/Update:

We will not be allowing parents to enter the building for pick up or drop off. We ask that you please remain in your vehicles during this process (unless you are unbuckling your child or something of that nature).

Thank you!

post_text:
Good Morning Hematite Families!

There will be a 5th grade open house on Wednesday, August 26th at 6:30 pm. We ask families to please wear masks and meet in the Auditorium. Our 5th grade class is small this year, so we feel we can social distance and stay safe during this open house. (You should have received or will receive a letter this week regarding the 5th grade open house) 5th graders will be getting their schedules and can bring school supplies to their lockers.

We also invite all new students who want to tour the building to call the office and let us know if you would like to come during this time as well.

If you have not called the office to notify us that your students will be staying home, online this year, we ask that you please do so this week. We are busy preparing for our online academy. We will let you know all these details soon!

School starts on Monday, August 31st at 11:30 am for the High school and Middle School.

See you all soon!

We are back in the office getting ready for the 2020-2021 School Year. There are a lot of phone numbers and email addresses missing and/or needing to be updated in power-school. If you have any questions, please contact me kmajor@ishpemingschools.com

Have a great August!

post_text:
The Ishpeming Public School District will be providing meals at the Pearl Street entrance of the Ishpeming High/Middle Complex, starting July 6, 2020, on Mondays and Thursdays from 11:00 am -12:30 pm.

The meals provided on Monday will be breakfast and lunch. We will provide enough meals to cover Monday - Wednesday.

On Thursday the meals that will be provided are breakfast and lunch & we will provide enough meals for Thursday thru Sunday.

Due to Covid-19 State officials have advised that children will not be able to eat were the meals are being distributed.
Parents or Guardians may pick up meals for their children.

If you should have any questions or concerns please contact Calvin Attwell by email cattwell@ishpemingschools.com or by phone (906) 475-7803 ext.110.

Thank you for your continued support of the Ishpeming Public School District.

shared_text:
Becky LaBrecque is with Kevin Bell and 19 others.
April 22 at 10:27 AM ¬∑

One month ago today I had an idea.üí°

I discovered a need that felt too big to fill alone.

1000 3D printed face shields were needed!
I knew my colleagues would help. And I have network marketing skillsüòé. So I went to work!

I had no idea it would grow into this.
The network grew so quickly. Makers from all over the region rallied. Word spread. People I never met before joined in and went full throttle towards our goal.

More organizations and businesses reached out for our help. üôè
And even more stepped up to donate and support our work.üí™

As of today this crew has turned in 4,151 3D printed face shields which were distributed all over the Upper Peninsula. And this graphic doesn't even show all the efforts around the U.P.! This is just the little effort that I sparked with a little social media magic. ‚ù§Ô∏èüôè
#thankful #UPStrong #MichiganStrong #WeAreMakers #YooperMakersUnited #3Dprintedfaceshields #3DprintedPPE #SeeWhatNetworkMarketingCanDo #BeTheLight #HelpOthers #SupportYourCommunity

I tagged a few of the makers here. If I missed you, please tag yourself!

To help better serve the families in our community, the Ishpeming Public School District will be expanding their locations for picking up breakfast/lunch combo packs!

Beginning Monday - 3/30 - throughout the school closure - each Monday & Thursday, from 11:00 am - 1:00 pm parents may also pick up breakfast/lunch combo packs at Christ the King - 440 Stoneville Road - Ishpeming.

Parents have the option of picking up multiple combos for multiple children. Parents may also pick up enough combos to sustain their children for multiple days.

Combos are FREE for anyone 18 years old or younger & EVERYONE is welcome!

Combos will continue to be available at the IMS/IHS Pearl Street entrance -Monday thru Friday - 11:00 am - 1:00 pm.

post_text: Reminder to all Hematite Power Pack Students, Parents and Guardians.
shared_text:
Hematite Power Packs
March 17 at 11:02 AM ¬∑

‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏èSPECIAL ANNOUNCEMENT FROM HEMATITE POWER PACKS‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è

In the wake of the extended school closure implemented by Governor Whitmer, Hematite Power Packs is still going to be available to our students at Ishpeming Public School. We have worked with Ishpeming Public Schools to have a pick up plan for our Power Packs.

If you are a student or family that receives a Hematite Power Pack each week, your pack will be available for pick up at Ishpeming Middle/High School, at the Pearl Street entrance, during lunch pick up from 11:00-1:00pm on Thursday and Friday. Please tell the person working that you also receive a Power Pack and they will bring one to you for the weekend. These will be available each week until school resumes as normal.

If you find yourself quarantined, and you are not able to pick up your pack, please privately message our Facebook page and we will see about delivering to your home.

During these uncertain times, we at Hematite Power Packs want to help alleviate some worry for our students.

It takes a village, and we live in the best one!

Sooo I have a very serious request and I really need some help! Tomorrow(Thursday) St. Vinnies and The Ishpeming Salvation Army will be getting a huge truck that we need help unloading. Usually our buddies from Hartman High help us(they ROCK) but with school being canceled both our organizations are in serious need of some help! The food we receive from this truck will help us feed our friends and neighbors for the next 3 months. If you can help PLEASE call us at 486-8121 or show up. Vinnies shipment is at 8:00 a.m. and ours is right after at 9:00a.m. Thanks in advance, and remember we are YOOPER STRONG!!
